ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would say the GG 550 was a course that looked into many topics involving metamorphic rocks such as diffusion and fluid flow. I would recommend the course to anyone wanted a better understanding of metamorphic processes or fluid transport in the deep crust.
I recommend this course to another student because Jay is a very nice teacher. This course could give you a basic idea of the processes and mechanism about the petrogenesis of mountain building.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: This course discusses a lot about the mass transfer, and it gives you a basic idea of the nature of petrogenesis of mountain building. I think it will help me in my future research.
